Ad Text:
We're partnering with a major player in financial services undergoing a multi-stream transformation program. As part of this uplift, we're seeking a Business Analyst who can also work comfortably in project management to support the delivery of several initiatives focused on frameworks, standards, capability uplift, tooling and operating model improvements across the organisation.

This is an opportunity to join a high-performing delivery function working on meaningful, enterprise-impacting change.

In this role, you will:

Manage end-to-end delivery of uplift initiatives across frameworks, standards, capability, tooling and process improvement
Create and maintain high-quality project documentation, reporting, RAID logs, governance packs and delivery artefacts
Work closely with SMEs, tech teams, process owners and business stakeholders to align on scope, requirements, and outcomes
Facilitate workshops, drive clarity and support analysis where deeper BA involvement is needed
Identify and manage risks, issues, dependencies and ensure timely communication to stakeholders
Influence and coordinate across multiple business areas within a complex, federated environment
Ensure initiatives align to broader organisational strategy and uplift objectives

You will be well suited to this role if you have:

Demonstrated experience and success as a Business Analyst, ideally with hands-on project management experience
Experience delivering framework, standards, capability uplift, regulatory, operating model, risk or process improvement initiatives
Ability to work across both business and technology teams
Strong stakeholder engagement and the ability to build alignment across competing priorities
Experience working within structured delivery frameworks or transformation offices
Strong organisational skills, structured thinking, and a proactive approach to delivery
Ability to "roll up your sleeves" where deeper analysis or documentation is required

If you're a delivery-focused Business Analyst who can also operate as a Project Manager and you enjoy frameworks, structure and capability uplift work, this is a great opportunity for you.

Contact Nick Largent for more information.

Category:
Business/Systems Analysts (Information & Communication Technology)

Ad Text:
Business Intelligence Developer
Employment Type: Temporary Full Time (11 months)
Position Classification: Health Manager Level 4
Remuneration: $147,653 - $175,917, plus Superannuation
Location: 1 Reserve Road, St Leonards NSW
Hours Per Week: 38 
Requisition ID: REQ618760
Closing Date: Friday 21 November 2025 (11:59PM)

Join our Information Management and Quality team at Ministry of Health for an exciting temporary employment opportunity and be part of the team enriching health in millions of ways every day.  

About us 

We are committed to your growth and development, providing the resources and opportunities you need to excel in your career.
Our core values of collaboration, openness, respect, and empowerment are more than just words – they're the guiding principles that shape every aspect of our work.
Join a passionate team dedicated to innovation and creativity.

To learn more about the Ministry and what benefits we offer, access our Employee Benefits Handbook.

About the role
With your skills and experience, you can contribute to the millions of ways we’re enhancing health and wellness while developing your career as part of the largest health organisation in Australia. 

Health Manager level 4 starting salary from $147,653 - $175,917plus Super, with a 38- hour work week.

What you’ll be doing

Collaborate with stakeholders to understand business processes and translate them into data requirements.
Lead the design and development of data models and data marts to support efficient reporting and analysis.
Manage ETL processes to ensure accurate, secure, and timely data integration from multiple sources.
Monitor and optimise BI solution performance, ensuring fast and reliable data access.
Stay current with BI technologies and propose enhancements to improve solution effectiveness.

About you
We are seeking motivated and committed individuals who can support the work of NSW Health with:

You hold a degree or diploma in Information Technology (or equivalent experience).
You have strong knowledge of data warehousing, dimensional modelling, and performance tuning using T-SQL and execution plans.
You bring hands-on experience with SSIS, SQL Server (2012+), and source control tools like GIT.
You’re comfortable working in Agile and DevOps environments, with exposure to Microsoft Azure and Power BI.
You’re a strong communicator and problem-solver, capable of working independently or as part of a team.

How to apply
At The Ministry of Health, we want you to make the most of the opportunities you’ll get to grow your skills and your career, surrounded by authentic, smart people and leaders.

Please review the role description and submit your up-to-date resume (up to 5 pages) and cover letter (1-2 pages) and explaining your interest and motivation in applying for this role and highlighting your relevant skills.

For role related queries or questions contact Harkanwal Singh on harkanwal.singh@health.nsw.gov.au and quote REQ618760

If you do require any adjustments to the recruitment process during the recruitment process, please contact Lisa Byrne on lisa.byrne@health.nsw.gov.au 

Closing Date: 11:59pm Friday 21 November 2025

Our commitment to Diversity and Inclusion
At the Ministry of Health, we are committed to creating a diverse, inclusive and flexible environment which reflects the community and customers we serve. We actively promote the employment of women, people with a disability, Aboriginal and Torres Strait Islander peoples, LGBTIQ+ community and people from culturally and linguistically diverse backgrounds.

If you identify as Aboriginal or Torres Strait Islander and would like assistance with your application or to obtain more information on how to apply, please visit The Stepping Up Initiative.

To be eligible for employment in these roles you must be an Australian citizen, or a permanent resident of Australia, or a New Zealand citizen with a current New Zealand Passport, or hold a valid visa with permission to work in Australia.

Additional information

This is a temporary role and there may be opportunities for ongoing employment at grade.
This recruitment may be used to create a Talent Pool for similar future roles (ongoing or temporary) that may arise over the next 18 months.
Please note the selection process will include a range of merit-based techniques to assist in determining your suitability for the role.


For more information about working at the NSW Health, please visit our career portal.
